##Special Report | medical protective clothing emergency, but Hubei Xiantao only approved the production of 10 companies

Hey, guys

Function description, here is the "First Finance" magazine (predecessor "first finance weekly") readers club, we discover wonderful business value for you, also invited you to explore the bright business world.

On one side is the government-selected factory emergency expansion capacity, on the other side, a number of main export of medical protective clothing factories because there is no "domestic" qualification, has been asked to stop production.

By Xiao Wenjie

Editor | Wang Shanshan

Medical Protective clothing is one of the most urgent medical materials for epidemic prevention in Wuhan, Hubei and even the whole country. One of the country's largest production bases for the product is in Xiantao, Hubei Province. People's Daily Online reported on February 8 that the local government had issued a "military decree" to raise the daily production of medical protective clothing in the city from the previous 5,000 to 30,000 pieces within 10 days until February 8, and this task for Xiantao is "a great test" , because "most non-woven fabric enterprises to do foreign trade, holding domestic protective clothing production qualification is very little.

However, Xiantao this "non-woven home" in the medical protective clothing on the production capacity does not seem to be fully utilized. Since February, a number of factories have been ordered not to start work by the enterprise production team of the city's new pneumonia epidemic prevention and control headquarters.

One of the companies, which mainly produces non-woven fabrics and medical protective clothing for export, confirmed to Yimagazine that on February 3, Xiantao's market regulator cited "the rectification of the production order of non-woven fabric enterprises in the city" , companies that stopped production were told that demand from Hubei and Wuhan would be co-ordinated by the government. The factory was contacting workers to try to get back to work as soon as possible.

The basis for the "clean-up" came from a local document. On February 4, the enterprise production team of the Xiantao COVID-19 infectious pneumonia prevention and control headquarters issued an "information note on further standardizing the Production Order of non-woven Fabric Enterprises" (hereinafter referred to as the note) , we have identified 60"key manufacturing enterprises of epidemic prevention and control materials" , including 10 enterprises designated by the provincial government for the production of medical protective clothing and 28 enterprises for the production of disposable medical masks that meet the national standards, and 22 for the above 38 enterprises to provide raw materials, printing, packaging and other supporting production enterprises.

It is also the 10 companies on the list that are responsible for producing 30,000 suits a day. Outside this scope other non-woven fabric production enterprises, first of all are required to strictly in accordance with the provisions of Hubei Province against the outbreak of production shutdown. At the same time, there have been a number of foreign trade orders have been engaged in the production of non-woven fabric enterprises, because they have not applied for the relevant qualifications required for domestic sales, have become the object of this production order, production rectification.

In order to rapidly increase production capacity to 30,000 units per day, Xiantao's approach is to focus on the above-mentioned designated enterprises to give a lot of resources to support, in many parts of the unified management, to help enterprises increase production capacity. Local banks have extended loans of more than 370 million yuan to related enterprises. On the other hand, a lot of export capacity can not be used, including a number of first-line doctors approved protective clothing.

According to the instructions, the reorganization, which aims to ensure key points, quality and supply, will target four types of enterprises:

1) non-woven fabric enterprises without medical device production license and medical device product registration certificate (hereinafter referred to as "two certificates") ;

2) non-woven fabric enterprises with "two certificates" but substandard production environment;

3) it is not a designated production and supporting enterprise;

4) non-woven fabric enterprises which possess export qualification but do not meet the requirements of export to domestic sales.

The manufacture and sale of medical protective clothing, face masks and other products in China requires a medical device manufacturing license issued by the FDA. Companies that deal only in exports do not have those documents.

Non-woven fabric is the main material of producing medical disposable mask and medical protective clothing. More than 100 non-woven fabrics are produced locally, but more than 90 per cent of their products (not limited to medical ones) are exported, according to figures from Xiantao's economic and Trade Commission for 2018, only 2 have the qualification of producing and selling medical protective clothing in China. Application Standards and the domestic hospital sales channels of the special barriers, is a large number of non-woven fabric enterprises to apply for the domestic market will not be strong reason. Many manufacturers export medical protective clothing, although their products do not meet domestic standards, but meet the standards of Japan, the United States or the European Union.

The unnamed company told China Business News Yimagazine that on January 25 the company had sent thousands of protective clothing from its inventory to hospitals such as Wuhan Union Medical College through private volunteers, the doctor will open the case on the spot to confirm whether the protective clothing meets the requirements. The receiving doctor's feedback is that the quality of these protective clothing is higher than the National Standard and can be used in isolation ward, ICU, laboratory and other environments. The company can produce more than 5,000 sets of protective suits a day with sufficient staff and raw materials.

On January 31 this year, the State Council issued a notice requesting the urgent import of Japanese, American and European Standard Medical Protective clothing. According to Wang Jiangping, Vice Minister of Industry and Information Technology, China has the capacity to export 50,000 sets of medical protective clothing that do not meet Chinese standards every day. MIIT will "promote the alignment of export standards with Chinese standards so that export products meeting EU and US standards can be used in some areas of China" .

Even without a shake-up, it would be hard for the company to restore its usual capacity on its own. Since the outbreak of the new crown pneumonia in Wuhan, the factory has been receiving a large number of enterprises and individuals to purchase demand, and mostly for donation purposes. But during the Spring Festival holiday, many of the workers have returned to their hometowns, mostly in Hubei, and even if they are willing to return to work, traffic control makes it difficult for them to return to the factory in time.

The company told Yimagazine that market regulators had explained when they shut down its factories that part of the motivation for the crackdown was to prevent factories with no qualifications and products up to standard from producing them privately and selling them at high prices, disrupt the production order. The company said it understands and supports the government's intention to regulate production, but hopes that this "one-size-fits-all" approach will change.

At present, Hubei and the whole country are in the key period of fighting the epidemic, and many cities are in a state of shortage of consumptive medical supplies. Several volunteers who have direct contact with doctors in the isolation wards and fever clinics of designated hospitals in Wuhan told China Business News Yimagazine that while some key hospitals now have certain guaranteed supplies, many hospitals are still in urgent need of protective supplies, protective clothing in particular, "repeated use, with a disposable raincoat to replace the situation is not uncommon. ".

The medical mask industry, which is also facing this dilemma, has been supported by the Special Task Force. On February 2, the COVID-19 and the Drug Administration jointly issued a statement saying that before the end of the pneumonia outbreak, the import and export of masks not listed on the domestic market are allowed to be sold in the provincial market. Prior to this, Shenzhen has adopted an emergency filing mechanism. For those enterprises that originally produced foreign standard masks for export, but were able to produce domestic standard masks but did not obtain the relevant qualification, the filing shall be completed within one day after the products have passed the inspection.

However, designated hospitals are not included in the temporary regulation of "Special Treatment" , as medical protective clothing is the most needed and scarce material for medical staff.
